============================================================================
 Phase 3b — YBCO Meissner shield attenuation analysis
============================================================================

v4 geometry: shield t = 10.0 μm, pitch P = 20 μm, column height h = 100 μm
YBCO at 77 K: London penetration depth λ_L ≈ 200 nm

Contributions to attenuation:
  London penetration (d/λ_L = 50):  434 dB (theoretical max)
  Edge leakage over shield top (h=100 μm, P=20 μm):  20.8 dB

Defect-limited attenuation (dominates in practice):

  Film quality                         Attenuation
  Conservative (commercial 2G tape)         80 dB
  Mid-quality (research-grade PLD)         100 dB
  High-quality (SQUID-grade)               120 dB

Net attenuation (min of theoretical and defect-limited):

  Conservative (commercial 2G tape)  : 80 dB  (PASS (>80 dB))
  Mid-quality (research-grade PLD)   : 100 dB  (PASS (>80 dB))
  High-quality (SQUID-grade)         : 120 dB  (PASS (>80 dB))

Compared to DAC noise floor:
  16-bit DAC LSB: 20·log10(1/65536) = -96 dB
  For Meissner shield to be "no longer a budget item":
    need attenuation > 96 dB (puts crosstalk below DAC quantization)

Pitch sensitivity (defect-limited, conservative 1e8 quality):
  P =   5 μm  →  attenuation = 80 dB
  P =  10 μm  →  attenuation = 80 dB
  P =  20 μm  →  attenuation = 80 dB
  P =  50 μm  →  attenuation = 80 dB
  P = 100 μm  →  attenuation = 80 dB

